  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;divination&nbsp;[good];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;cleric/oracle 2, inquisitor 1, paladin 1;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 minute<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S, F (a silver hand mirror worth 50 gp)<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;one good-aligned creature<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 day<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Will negates (harmless);&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>The Lantern Bearers must often make difficult decisions during their missions, such as determining what to do with captured enemies-should they be executed, imprisoned, set free, or given a chance to mend their ways? With this spell, you grant a creature the ability to foresee moral consequences, as if the creature were wearing a <i>phylactery of faithfulness</i>. The spell's guidance focuses on the protection of beauty and encourages peaceful resolution and mercy.</p>\n</div>\n",
